                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="465053" author="adilger" created="Sat, 26 Jul 2025 01:36:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are still a large number of subtests being skipped on ZFS since the introduction of default compression on ZFS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once the test system hiatus is behind us, these should be tested with ZFS to confirm they are actually working again (with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;/dev/urandom&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; during writes), or understand why they are failing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="450293" author="simmonsja" created="Fri, 28 Mar 2025 20:22:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18728&quot; title=&quot;sanity/test_413a and conf-sanity/test_32[b,c,e,h] permanent timeout/failures with ZFS back-end only&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18728&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18728&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; cover this as well. Since you reopened this then I will close the other ticket then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="449670" author="adilger" created="Tue, 25 Mar 2025 17:52:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are still dozens of tests listed in the conf-sanity always_except list for this ticket:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;if [[ &quot;$mds1_FSTYPE&quot; == &quot;zfs&quot; ]]; then
        always_except LU-18652 108a 112a 112b 113 117 119 121 122a
        always_except LU-18652 123aa 123ab 123ac 123ad 123ae 123af 123ag 123ah 123ahi   
        always_except LU-18652 123F 123G 123H 126 129 132 133 135 136 137 150 152 153a 153b 153c 155 802a
fi 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A patch is needed to remove these exceptions (if they pass) and/or move them to another LU ticket (if a different issue is causing them to fail) before this ticket should be closed.  We shouldn&apos;t have closed tickets in Jira with the &lt;tt&gt;always_except&lt;/tt&gt; label.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="448971" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 20 Mar 2025 01:30:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/58115&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/58115&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18728&quot; title=&quot;sanity/test_413a and conf-sanity/test_32[b,c,e,h] permanent timeout/failures with ZFS back-end only&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18728&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18728&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: use urandom to really consume ZFS space&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) resolved this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="444966" author="adilger" created="Wed, 19 Feb 2025 05:58:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is the compression property not persistent in the fileset once it is set?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="444921" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 18 Feb 2025 20:55:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Some of the conf-sanity still fail even with compression is off. I think the reason for the conf-sanity 32 test are failing is that zfs import is used directly without turn off compression. That is my theory&#160; but I haven&apos;t tried my idea of turning off compression for the import.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="444903" author="adilger" created="Tue, 18 Feb 2025 19:32:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I thought this was related to James&apos; compression patch, but I&apos;m not sure that it is?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="444522" author="simmonsja" created="Fri, 14 Feb 2025 03:13:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still need to work out the issue to re-enable the test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="443812" author="simmonsja" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2025 13:42:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have a patch to quite the errors. &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57990/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57990/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="443808" author="emoly.liu" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2025 13:13:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maloo search says this issue happened 71 times in the past week.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="443762" author="emoly.liu" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2025 02:09:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on master: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/788a61c4-7e49-4c7d-802e-b5874d7fa277&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/788a61c4-7e49-4c7d-802e-b5874d7fa277&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
